uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.store

Interface IRegenInstance

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    IRegenInvalidInstance, IRegenValidInstance

    public interface IRegenInstance
    Represents a specific IFrame/ISlot network that has been regenerated from a serialized form, and hence may be partially or fully invalid with respect to the current model.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<IRegenPath> getAllPrunedPaths()
      Provides list of any slots or slot-values that have been pruned from the network as a result of updates to the model since the instance was serialised.
      java.util.List<IRegenPath> getPrunedSlotPaths()
      Provides list of any slots that have been pruned from the network as a result of updates to the model since the instance was serialised.
      java.util.List<IRegenPath> getPrunedValuePaths()
      Provides list of any slot-values that have been pruned from the network as a result of updates to the model since the instance was serialised.
      IFrame getRootFrame()
      Provides root-frame of fully or partially valid network.
      CIdentity getRootTypeId()
      Provides root-frame type identity, which may or may not represent a currently valid CFrame (see getStatus()).
      IRegenStatus getStatus()
      Provides the status of the instance with respect to the current model.
